  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nRunning cut-v0.3.0, when importing keys, assuming /var/lib/lighthouse exists and is given as a --datadir, the validator will not create the validator_definitions.yml file under it.\r\n\r\n```\r\nyorick@ethlinux:~/eth2-zinken-lh$ docker-compose run validator-import\r\nDo all validator keys have the same password? (y/n) y\r\nRunning account manager for zinken testnet\r\nvalidator-dir path: \"/var/lib/lighthouse/validators\"\r\nUnable to open validator_definitions.yml: UnableToWriteFile(Os { code: 2, kind: NotFound, message: \"No such file or directory\" })\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe entrypoint looks like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n      - query-lh-validator-passwords.sh\r\n      - lighthouse\r\n      - account\r\n      - validator\r\n      - import\r\n      - --datadir\r\n      - /var/lib/lighthouse\r\n      - --directory\r\n      - /var/lib/lighthouse/validator_keys\r\n      - --testnet\r\n      - ${TESTNET}\r\n```\r\nwhere the shell script just decides whether to add `--reuse-password` to the command line and otherwise just runs `$@` as is.",
